denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Philip","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Greek name <i>Philippos</i>, meaning ‘lover of horses’, from <i>philein</i> ‘to love’ + <i>hippos</i> ‘horse’. This was popular in the classical period and since. It was the name of the father of  Alexander the Great . It was also the name of one of Christ's apostles, of a deacon ordained by the apostles after the death of Christ, and of several other early saints.  See also  Philippa ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":5,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":14,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":49,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Philip de Valletort was born about 1210, in North Tawton, Devon, England, his father, Joscelyn de Valletort, was 42 and his mother, Emma Botreaux, was 36. He married Joan de Cornwall before 1240, in Modbury, Devon, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died about 1259, in Devon, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 51, and was buried in Stowey, Somerset, England."},"et":{"Abt 1210–Abt 1259":"umbes 1210–umbes 1259","1210–1259":"1210–1259","1212–1300":"1212–1300","1240–1294":"1240–1294","1170–1230":"1170–1230","1175–1199":"1175–1199","1198":"1198","1230":"1230","Abt 1259":"umbes 1259","1175":"1175","1240":"1240","1294":"1294","1170":"1170","Bef 1240":"enne 1240","1215":"1215","1259":"1259","Abt 1300":"umbes 1300","1224":"1224","1300":"1300","1212":"1212","Abt 1210":"umbes 1210","1199":"1199","1210":"1210","Stowey, Somerset, England":"Stowey, Somerset, England","Modbury, Devonshire, England":"Modbury, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Tawton, Devon, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom",", , , England":"England","North Tawton, Devon, England":"North Tawton, Devon, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1210–Abt 1259":"noin 1210–noin 1259","1210–1259":"1210–1259","1212–1300":"1212–1300","1240–1294":"1240–1294","1170–1230":"1170–1230","1175–1199":"1175–1199","1198":"1198","1230":"1230","Abt 1259":"noin 1259","1175":"1175","1240":"1240","1294":"1294","1170":"1170","Bef 1240":"ennen vuotta 1240","1215":"1215","1259":"1259","Abt 1300":"noin 1300","1224":"1224","1300":"1300","1212":"1212","Abt 1210":"noin 1210","1199":"1199","1210":"1210","Stowey, Somerset, England":"Stowey, Somerset, England","Modbury, Devonshire, England":"Modbury, Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Tawton, Devon, England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta",", , , England":"England","North Tawton, Devon, England":"North Tawton, Devon, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fr":{"Abt 1210–Abt 1259":"environ 1210–environ 1259","1210–1259":"1210–1259","1212–1300":"1212–1300","1240–1294":"1240–1294","1170–1230":"1170–1230","1175–1199